1 Section 1. Chapter 244 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 3, each board
4 of county commissioners shall adopt an ordinance requiring the
5 owner or operator of a kennel, an animal rescue organization or a
6 commercial establishment engaged in the business of handling
7 animals, including, without limitation, a breeder, a cattery, a
8 retailer, a pet groomer or a dealer, to complete a training course
9 on handling animals in a manner prescribed by the board of
10 county commissioners.
11 2. Each owner or operator who is required to complete a
12 training course on handling animals pursuant to subsection 1
13 shall renew the training biennially in a manner prescribed by the
14 board of county commissioners.
15 3. The ordinance adopted by a board of county
16 commissioners pursuant to subsection 1 does not apply to:
17 (a) A business engaged exclusively in the handling of equine
18 animals;
19 (b) A veterinarian; or
20 (c) An animal shelter.
21 4. As used in this section:
22 (a) “Animal rescue organization” has the meaning ascribed to
23 it in NRS 574.205.
24 (b) “Animal shelter” has the meaning ascribed to it in
25 NRS 574.240.
26 (c) “Breeder” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 574.245.
27 (d) “Cattery” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 574.250.
28 (e) “Dealer” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 574.260.
29 (f) “Kennel” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 574.280.
30 (g) “Pet” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 574.300.
31 (h) “Pet groomer” means a person who professionally styles
32 pets for compensation. The term includes, without limitation, a
33 person who professionally bathes, brushes or clips a pet.
34 (i) “Retailer” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 574.320.
35 (j) “Veterinarian” has the meaning ascribed to it in
36 NRS 574.330.
